betterquesting:10.desc:8:
§o"If I want to get anything done, I'll need a good place to work."§r

Build a crafting table from 4 wooden planks.

§o"These wooden tools won't last long. I should try to craft something a bit more sturdy."§r

Mine some cobblestone, then craft a stone axe, pickaxe, and sword.

§oThe monsters which roam these lands at night are relentless. I should find a place which I can stay for the night.§r

Check this box once you have some sort of shelter. It could be anything: a house, a cave, a hole in the ground, or some renovated ruins.

§o"Now that I have some shelter, I should make it feel a bit more like home."§r

Complete this quest once you have a wooden chest, a crafting table, and some torches. Then, place them in your shelter.

§o"I'm running low on provisions. I should set up a small farm so I can grow my own food."

§rIn order to set up a farm, you'll need water and tilled land. Craft a hoe, and obtain some seeds from breaking tall grass.

§o"With a supply of raw food and an array of tools, I can prepare something much more fulfilling."

§rIt's time to bake bread! First, gather water, salt, and flour. Flour is made by crushing wheat with a mortar and pestle. Next, mix these items into dough with your mixing bowl. Finally, craft bread using dough and bakeware.

§o"In my travels I have come across lots of things I don't quite know how to use yet. I should put some of this "experience" I have been gaining towards being more skilled."

§rIn the inventory screen, click the "Skills" tab. Here, you can allocate XP levels towards gaining proficiency in different skills. Level up one of your skills and then check the box. Each first skill point costs 3 XP levels, and every point afterwards costs 1 more XP level than the last.

§nTIP:§r "Main" quests such as this one (see the fancy border) will open up new quest trees when completed.

§o"Eating too much of the same thing isn't great for my health. I should try to diversify my diet."

§rCollect an item from each food group: Apple (Fruit), Carrot (Veggie), Wheat (Grain), Beef (Protein), Milk (Dairy).

§o"With all this farm-fresh food I have, I could probably make something really tasty."

§rBake a cake.

§o"Travelling these lands, I've seen lots of different animals. It would probably be useful to keep some on my farm."

§rCraft a lead, then bring home a cow of any kind. Check the box once you have done this.

§o"Having a cow is great - now I have a permanant source of drinkable milk!"

§rCows eat wheat and grass, and require water to drink. Breed a cow (female) and bull (male) by feeding them both while they are near each other. Once the cow has given birth a calf, she will now produce milk. Keep your cow well-fed and happy until you are able to obtain milk with a bucket. Then, craft the bucket in a crafting table to create fresh milk. 

Fresh milk can be used in cooking recipes or crafted with an empty bottle to make a drinkable milk bottle to restore your thirst.

Fresian Cows - 5 bottles/bucket
Holstein Cows - 5 bottles/bucket
Jersey Cows - 5 bottles/bucket
Other Cows - 3 bottles/bucket
Sheep/Goats - 3 bottles/bucket

Different milks can also be made into cheese by placing them in a cheese mold.

§o"Even these stone tools are breaking pretty quickly. They also aren't very effective. Perhaps I can find a better material to make tools out of underground."

§rFind a cave, or start digging underground. Bring back some coal and copper ore.

§T§nTIP:§r Press "F" when holding a torch to switch it to your other hand! This makes it easier to see in the dark without switching to and from your pickaxe/weapon.

If this feature gives you performance issues, it can be disabled with "L".

§o"Great! Now that I have some better raw materials, time to get to work making some better tools."

§rBuild a furnace and smelt your ore into ingots. Then, use your ingots to craft a copper pickaxe.

§o"Underground, iron is abundant, but monsters are rampant. A suit of iron armor would go a long way for my survivability."

§rCraft a full set of copper armor.

§o"Now that I'm properly armed, I feel more confident in my ability to fight the monsters. Time to take revenge for my friends!"

§rKill 10 zombies.

§nTIP:§r The reward for this quest is a sword skill! Press the "P" key to access the sword skills menu.

§o"Dotted across the land, I have seen towers with staircases spiralling downward into darkness. From the black abyss, I hear the wails of an unimaginable number of monsters. Am I finally ready to take them on?"

§rFind a roguelike dungeon, and fight your way down in order to retrieve a §oLifeblood Crystal§r and raise your max health.

§o"In this world brimming with arcane energy, I've reached a crossroads. I must decide what magic discipline to devote my studies to, in order to become a true master of the arcane arts."

§rChoose one of the three §o§bMagic Disciplines §rto devote yourself to. This will dictate the type of magic you will be tasked to study, and unlock new crafting recipes for you.

§lMagic Disciplines:
§a- §lDruidity§r§a
    - Become one with nature, draw power from the earth itself
    - Unlocks recipes from: Botania, Roots, Nature's Aura

§5- §lArtificing§r§5
    - Manipulate matter and create magical devices to do your bidding
    - Unlocks recipes from: Thaumcraft, Astral Sorcery, Embers

§r§c- §lOccultism§r§c
    - Cast forbidden rituals and make pacts with unspeakable creatures
    - Unlocks recipes from: Blood Magic, Bewitchment, EnderIO

§rOnce you have made a choice, check the box on the right and select the tome corresponding to your magic discipline. Once you have obtained the book, right-click with it in hand to gain disciple's knowledge.

§n§oTIP:§r §oOnce becoming a "master" of your chosen discipline, you will gain the ability to continue studying and select an additional discipline. Eventually, you will be able to obtain all three disciplines.

§nTIP:§r§o If you do not wish to follow the class-based progression system, see the quest "about the pack" to learn how to enable "§e§oNo-Class Mode§r".

§o"With these advanced conductive metals, I could create the beginning of an electrical network. Finally, I can bring power to these untamed lands!"

§rCraft an engineer's hammer, then craft 4 LV wire coils and 4 LV wire connectors. Finally, craft a kinetic dynamo and a windmill.  The windmill goes on the dynamo's face with the square of conductive cabling.

§o"There is much more hidden underground than just Copper and Iron. I'm sure all of these metals will be useful at some point, so I should collect as much as I can."

§rMine a significant amount of tin, lead, silver, and aluminum.

Certain biomes have higher concentrations of different ores. While you can find any ore anywhere, exploring may help you find what you need.

§e§l§nExtra Ores:
§n§r§lCoal§r - §oSandy, Swamp
§r§lCopper§r - §oPlains, Hills, Mesa
§r§lIron§r -§o Hills, Mesa, Mountain
§r§lAluminum§r - §oPlains, Forest
§r§lNickel§r - §oForest, Sandy
§r§lTin§r §o- Snowy, Mountain
§r§lLead§r - §oMountain
§r§lSilver§r -§o Snowy, Swamp
§r§lGold§r -§o Sandy, Swamp
§r§lEmera§lld§r -§o Mountain
§r§lQuartz §r-§o Snowy
§r§lRedstone§r -§o Sandy
§r§lLapis§r -§o Ocean
§r§lCrystal§r -§o Magical, Mushroom
§r§lDiamond §r- §o???

§o"I should probably use some of this... if I get knocked out in the wilds, I will probably lose experience. But... who knows what I might need it for!"

§rHave 30 levels of experience at once.

§o"I have seen villages of traders before, and it's about time I located one. It would be useful to be able to barter for goods in this strange land."

§rFind a village, and meet a villager. Then, trade or fight monsters to aquire a silver coin.

Coins can be acquired from villagers or as loot from fallen monsters. 8 bronze coins = 1 silver coin, 8 silver coins = 1 gold coin, 8 gold coins = 1 platinum coin. You can use "/coins stack" to stack all coins in your inventory, and "/coins unstack" to unstack them.

§o"By crafting 8 emeralds around an empty bottle, I can create usable bottles of stored experience."

§rCraft some bottles o' enchanting.

§o§o"While looking at all these building blocks I've collected, a thought came to me. With a simple chisel, I could alter the look of these blocks to further decorate my home. Time to tap into my artistic side!"

§rCraft a chisel, and use the chisel inventory to turn stone brick into chiseled stone brick.

§o"Now that I have some pretty blocks, I should see about making some real furniture to spice up my home."

§rCraft two couches, an oak coffee table, and an oak bedside table.

§o"There are some things I would like to make for my home, but do not have simple crafting recipes for. With a bit chisel, I can make my own furniture, stairs, blocks, anything - all with bits and pieces of other blocks."

§rCraft an iron bit chisel, then chisel some cobblestone.

§o"An quicker method of aquiring food just came to me. If I can craft a fishing rod, I could pull my meals straight out of the water!"

§rCraft a fishing rod, then fish up any type of fish. Finally, craft your fish into fish cutlets.

§o"Rarely, I have found sparkling gemstones at the depths of the world. I'm sure I can put these exotic and valuable materials to good use, if I can find enough of them."

§rRetrieve 8 diamonds, 12 quartz, and 16 lapis lazuli, and 20 redstone dust.

§o"If I had a long-range weapon, I could take on the monsters with a lot less danger to myself. I should see about fashioning a bow and some arrows."

§rCraft a bow, and 16 arrows.

§o"... Why would you do this?"

§rHave 60 levels of experience at once. Please store it somewhere.

§o"Apparently, there are ways to use experience aside from levelling up. A villager priest told me that, by using something called an enchantment altar, you can empower your tools and armor, at the cost of experience. I should look into this."

§rCraft an enchantment altar, and some bookshelves to strengthen it.

§o"If I had a proper kitchen like back home, I could prepare food with ease. I should see about assembling a food prep area in my home."

§rCraft the following pieces of a kitchen, then assemble a kitchen multiblock structure.

§o"Now that the inside of my home looks nice, I should see about making the outside look more cozy as well."

§rCraft eight stone paths, a bird bath, a mailbox, and two park benches.

§o"After delving into the art of bit chiseling, the need for more sophisticated chisel tools became apparent. Let me see about making something to help."

§rCraft a diamond chisel, diamond bit saw, and chiseled fluid tank.

§o"I have lots of great things to eat now, but what about to drink? I bet I could fashion a fermenting barrel and brew some tasty beverages from the comfort of my home."

§rCraft a fermenting barrel and a bucket of ale wort. Then, brew a bottle of ale.

Other drinks can be brewed as well, many of which require the use of various fruits and a crushing tub.

§o"Every good engineer needs good tools... and a whole lot of metal."

§rCraft an engineer's hammer. The hammer can be used to activate certain machines and to craft metal plates. Also, collect a good amount of copper.

§o"Back home, I recall alchemists' shops in the city. Shimmering potions filled the displays in the front windows, but they were always exorbitantly priced. With proper brewing materials from the Nether, I could get a leg up on the monsters."

§rCraft a brewing stand, then brew a potion of healing with a water bottle + nether wart + glistening melon.

§o"I'm getting better at alchemy, but there are many potions I have left to discover."

§rBrew the 10 potions shown on the right. 
(Take note, some are enhanced potions with longer or stronger effects)

§o"I've gained a bit of combat experience fighting those zombies. Perhaps I could take care on some tougher foes now?"

§rSlay 25 skeletons, 20 spiders, and 10 creepers.

§o"Some alchemists brewed potions called elixirs, made from natural and commonly found materials. These elixirs, unlike standard potions, can stack up to 16. Having this skill would be useful."

§rCraft an alchemic condenser and two alchemic retorts. Assemble the condenser by placing the condenser body with two retorts on either side. Finally, brew an elixir of speed, an elixir of instant health, and an elixir of return.

§o"Some tasks, like moving ore into and out of my furnace, are becoming increasingly tedious. I should devise a way to automate this."

§rCraft 2 hoppers and 2 chests. Place one hopper facing into the top of your furnace, and place a chest on top of that hopper. Then, place another hopper directly below your furnace, with this hopper facing into another chest.

Now, if provided with fuel, any materials put in the top chest will be brought down into the furnace, cooked, and spit out into the bottom chest. Check the box once you have done this.

§o"I can't seem to make stairs or slopes out of every kind of block. Maybe I can find a way around this."

§rCraft 8 framed blocks. These can be filled with other kinds of blocks in order to make any variety of stairs, slopes, walls, or slabs you could want.

§o"This book is a botanist's guide to the flora of these lands. The sparkling flowers I've seen have powerful arcane properties. I should see about harnessing them."

§rCollect red, yellow, and blue magical flowers and turn them into petals. Then, craft a petal apothecary.

§o"The journal explains that the arcane and the cosmos are one, and with the right focusing tools, the power of the stars can be channelled. It also explains that the marble structures I've seen are observatories left behind by astral mages of the past."

§ As you readthe Journal, you hear an unfamiliar voice reverberate inside your mind.

§e§o"Look beneath the large marble fountain - bring a crafting table there. Go forth and unlock the power of the stars."

§rGather 1 aquamarine, and discover the secrets of a large marble observatory. Craft a resonating wand.

Upgrade your blood altar to tier III, then imbue a gold block at the altar to create a magician blood orb.

To construct a tier III blood altar, you will need to place blank runes one block below and two blocks out from the previous level - leaving a one block gap between which can be filled with any block. 5 blank runes will be placed on each side, leaving corners empty. At each corner, build upwards two blocks and then place a glowstone block atop the pillar. 

§oFor reference, see the images here:
§ehttps://ftb.gamepedia.com/Blood_Altar

Craft a Prospecting Pick. When clicking on a block with this item, it searches for ores in an 8 block radius around the block you click. This is very useful for finding§e large ore nodes§r which may be hiding in the surrounding stone.

§nTIP:§r Using a hammer makes searching for prospected ore much easier!

§o"With new materials from the Nether, I think I can come up with some improvements to my old alchemy station."

§rCraft an advanced alchemy condenser and 3 advanced retorts. Then, craft an elixir of iron skin and an elixir of health boost.

§o"I've mined a lot of things now, but a better tool would be nice. The best miners from back home used tools made of pure diamond crystal. It sounds expensive, but such a tool could cut through anything with ease. I should get my hands on one."

§rCraft a diamond pickaxe.

§o"Dotted across the land, I've encountered crumbling obsidian structures. This stone has infamous occult properties. The knowledge of how to enter the underworld is commonplace, but it's practice is forbidden. Do I dare build the gateway and enter?"

§rGather 14 obsidian and craft a portal, or find an intact portal on the surface. Craft a vertical ring of obsidian blocks with a 2x3 width/height opening or larger. Then, light the bottom blocks of the opening with flint and steel. Lastly, enter the Nether.

§o"I've noticed an odd phenomenon while diving the various caves nearby my camp. As I descend into the depths I find the atmosphere growing warmer and warmer close to bedrock. I believe one of my texts makes note of this phenomenon, and I may be able to isolate where it's coming from"§r

Consult the ancient tablet and make yourself an atmospheric gauge and an ember bore. Then, harvest a shard of ember from deep underground.

§o"I've read about a land called The Beneath, a dark and hostile cave system deep below the bedrock layer. Apparently the monsters which reside there are extremely powerful, but the treasures of the earth are abundant."§r

Create a portal to The Beneath, and travel to the pitch-black realm at the center of the earth.

The Beneath contains more powerful monsters than the overworld, but they drop extra loot and experience. The Beneath is also filled with ores and riches for those brave enough to face the darkness.

§o"Amazing! There seems to be an innate energy within the very bedrock on which the world rests! There was once a great civilization here, large enough to compare to the Astrals, which utilized this Ember energy. I should begin researching these crystals as soon as possible."§r

Consult your ancient codex and craft yourself an ember activator, a copper cell to store ember, an ember emitter, and an ember receptor. This will be your basic ember power generation setup.

§o"In my travels I have come across various signs of the ancient Dwarven civilization that pioneered the application of Ember in machinery. Though the Dwarves are long gone, their machinations remain. They even seemed to have created life with this energy, truly remarkable! Perhaps by dismantling these ancient golems, I will learn more of Dwarven society"§r

Defeat 4 Ancient Golems. Beware, they are dangerous foes, and will not be knocked back by attacks. They can also fire beams of ember from range.

§o"Those charred black skeletons hold a dangerous secret. With 3 of their skulls and a bit of soul sand, I think I could summon something..."

§rCollect 3 wither skeleton skulls. Then, fight and defeat the Wither.

§o"The denizens of this place are ruthless and tough to kill, but perhaps I can find some use for thier loot."

§rKill 10 blazes, 10 magma cubes, and 5 salamanders.

§o"Sometimes, while I'm exploring, I still want to pass some time. A sleepig bag would be perfect for this!"

§rCraft a sleeping bag.

§o"Consuming the lifeheart crystal made me feel a lot healthier. I should try to find more of these."

§rMax out your health by using 5 lifeheart crystals.
Craft a grappling hook.
Craft a waystone.

Craft a hang glider.

When deployed, the hang glider allows you to glide through the air with great speed. For best results, try using it from a high place, such as a mountain top.

Craft an ender launcher.

This item, when used, launches you in the direction you are looking with great speed. This can be useful to propel yourself forward quickly across a plain, or straight up into the air to get some height for your hang-glider. Beware, the launcher does nothing to protect you from fall damage, and can be very dangerous if one is not careful when using it!

Craft a pair of long-fall boots.

These boots provide complete fall damage immunity, keeping you safe when flinging yourself through the air at high velocity.

Aquire an elytra.

Elytras can be equipped in the chest slot or the baubles body slot. They allow pseudo-flight via gliding. The higher your momentum, the further you can fly! Setting off a firework when in the air will also give you a boost of momentum, prolonging your flight.

Craft the Rending Gale.

The rending gale consumes feathers, and grants its weilder the power of flight!... Kind of. Crouch + right click will cause this item to begin consuming feathers in the inventory to build charge. When left clicking, you will be propelled through the air in the aimed direction very quickly. This is useful for scaling mountains and travelling long distances fast, but make sure you have a good source of feathers for your trip.

The rending gale has some other functions as well. Crouch + left clicking will cycle between flight, push, and pull modes. In push mode, mobs will be repelled when clicked. In pull mode, mobs will be sucked in towards you.
Craft an advanced hang-glider. Compared to the standard glider, these are much much faster and are also unbreakable!

By gaining knowledge of the arcana §lDruidity§r, a world of natural magic has opened to you!

§lYou may now:§r
- Craft items from §oBotania§r
- Craft items from §oNature's Aura§r
- Craft items from §oRoots§r
- Harvest §oRoots§r foragables from tall grass, crops
- See §oBotania§r flowers and mushrooms
- Find §oBotania§r loot in chests
- Craft unique Druid's wings
Find a forest mansion, defeat the inhabitants, and aquire a totem of undying.
Find an ocean monument, and slay an elder guardian.
Find a stronghold, activate the ender portal, and travel to the end.
Craft and use a boat.
Find a draft stallion and ride it using a riding crop.
Kill the Ender Dragon and collect its egg.
Craft a diamond sword, shield, and a full set of diamond armor.
Raid an end city.
Craft a motorboat.

§o"Ember activators are all well and good, but I believe I can increase efficency quite drastically. Using designs gleemed from my Dwarven texts, I have devised what I call the Pressure Refinery."§r

The Pressure Refinery is an advanced Ember Activator that must be given water in its lower input, as well as ember shards in its upper input. Craft the Pressure Refinery, as well as a block of Copper to conduct heat. By placing the refinery atop the copper block, and surrounding the copper block with fire or lava on each face, you will maximize the amount of ember extracted from each shard.

§o"I've recently been finding myself short on metals. Furnaces are well and good for cooking food and firing clay, but they leave somthing to be desired when it comes to processing ore. The Dwarves were master metalworkers; I'm sure there's some way to use their Ember energy to smelt metal more efficently"

§rCraft a melter, stamp base, and a stamper to begin advanced metal processing. Metal ore and embers are provided to the melter, which will melt the ore into a liquid. This liquid can be piped into the stamp base, and when you provide the top of the stamper with ember and a stamp made from caminite it will begin to produce stamped metal.

§o"I've run into a roadblock in my work. It seems mundane materials like copper and iron simply cannot conduct ember well enough to progress. My research indicates the Dwarves had devised a special alloy comprised of copper and gold, infused with ember, that was used in the creation of their greatest machines. This 'dawnstone' exhibits some very strange properties. It's fairly strong, and can be used in the creation of tools. Mundane tools seem to be a waste, though, as the machines created with dawnstone are much more interesting."

§rCraft a mixer centrifuge, then use it to create a dawnstone ingot. The mixer centrifuge is powered by ember, and is used to combine metals into an alloy. By piping in equal parts copper and gold, dawnstone is created. The molten dawnstone can then be piped to a stamp base to be formed into ingots or plates. Consult the Ancient Codex for more information.

§o"As of late it seems my work tools are lacking. Perhaps if I was able to use my new Dawnstone alloy while working with more mundane materials I would be able to achieve greater precision."

§rCraft a Dawnstone Anvil for making repairs to your gear. The dawnstone anvil is used by placing damaged gear and it's repair material on the anvil, and holding right click with your tinker's hammer. After a few strikes the gear will be fully repaired no matter how damaged it was. You can also use the anvil to break down salvaged gear into it's base components based on it's durability.

Aquire a golden fishing rod, which allows for fishing inside lava.

Then, catch some exotic fish in the nether!

Chickens eat seeds, and require a pool of water to drink from. Seeds can be placed on the ground, where chickens will peck at it. Seeds can also be placed directly from a hopper or dropper.

Hens need nests in which to lay their eggs. Eggs will become fertilized and hatch into baby chicks if a Rooster is nearby. Chickens of any sort will shed feathers over time.

Craft a nest, then collect 3 eggs and 5 feathers.

Sheep will graze for grass, flowers, and some crops. They will eat wheat from a trough and need water to drink.

Adult sheep can be sheared for wool. If a ewe has given birth, it can also be milked for sheep milk. Gather both white and black wool, and a bucket of sheep milk.

Pigs like to eat slop, carrots, beets, and potatoes, and also need water to drink. They love having mud to roll around in to be happy. Craft some mud and a bucket of slop.

Pigs, like all animals, can be killed for their meat. Pigs will also dig up truffles periodically if taken into a forest biome. You can walk a pig on a lead through a forest, or place a pen there.

Pigs can also be ridden using a carrot on a stick.
Cook up a §o§lSuper Omelette
Craft a blender, and use it to make fruit crush. Fruit crush is made using 2 apples and 4 melons.

§o"I can infuse the very stone and wood with magical essence!"
§r
Create a Pure Daisy in your new Petal Apothecary using 4 white petals and water, then throw in a seed.  Place stone and wood nearby to create 4 Livingwood, and 4 Livingrock.

§o§o§o"There must be some way to collect and harness this power flow I can sense..."§r

Craft a Mana Spreader which can send mana, as well as a Mana Pool to receive it.

The mana pool can transform items dropped inside, imbuing them with mana. It can also charge a Mana Tablet, providing mana to equipment when held.
Cook a Thanksgiving dinner, sit down, and have a feast to celebrate your mastery over hunger.

Have three full bars of health (30 hearts).

§n§oTIP§r: §oThis feat can be done a number of ways. Things that increase your health: max lifeheart crystals (base 10 hearts + 10 extra), a potion of health boost (+2 hearts per level), 5 nutrients above 90% (+1 heart each), a fulfilled food craving (+6 hearts), health-boosting qualities on trinkets (+1 heart per trinket), and the ring of odin (+10 hearts).

§o"My studies have brought me to, as far as I can tell, the ultimate refinement of the embersmith's craft: ember alchemy. Simply setting up this advanced crafting station will require me to use all my knowledge of Dwarven civilization. This will be no small task."

§rBegin your ember alchemy setup. You will first need to craft an exchange tablet, a beam cannon, and five alchemy pedestals. Arrange the alchemy pedestals around the exchange tablet, and situate the beam cannon to point towards the tablet. When charged by ember the cannon will fire a blast that kickstarts alchemy recipes.

§o"Why is it that my sandwich is always UNDER spools of wire?  That's it, time to make a better solution."
§r
Craft an Engineer's Toolbox to better keep organized.

§o"Seems like I could come up with a million uses for this stuff.  I'd better stock up."§r

Build a stockpile of steel.

§o"Hmm, maybe if I stuff this thing with MORE lead, I can get it to work better."§r

Create MV equipment. MV wiring requires a matching MV connector or relay in order to avoid fires and wire burnouts.

§o"So, it appears if I run MV through LV, the... uh... wire might burn?  Maybe I can fix that."
§r
MV Voltage is useful, but some devices need a safer voltage.  A Transformer can help adjust between them.

§o"What do you mean I can't pump 100,000 volts through this switch?"
§r
When using HV power, there are many cases where you may want to shut off current to a portion of your electric grid. However, a simple breaker switch is not well enough insulated for HV use. Craft a redstone breaker, which can be controlled via redstone signal and is compatible with HV power.

§o"With just a few new adjustments, I think I can really get the power humming."§r

Max out your power capacity and carrying capacity with High-Voltage equipment.

Craft 8 electrum ingots using your alloy forge.

Electrum is a highly conductive alloy, and is widely used in electrical wiring.

Make at least 8 constantan ingots using your alloy forge. 

Constantan is known for maintaining its resistivity over a range of temperatures, making it useful in the creation of thermoelectric generators.

§o"There must be a way to create more of this power.  Some of the flowers felt like... they're hungry, but yet, they give off power..."
§r
Create an §eEndoflame§r and experiment with feeding it burnables.

§o"New idea.  What happens if I take a really long spike of something metallic and fire it at extreme speeds through a creeper...."§r

Craft a railgun.  You'll also want a Charging Station and some ammo.

§o"I can't quite get the belts to feed the steel beast I built.  Maybe if I make some adjustments, I could automate it.  While I'm at it, I might have some ideas for making it faster."
§r
Time to break down the Blast Furnace and improve it with some of the steel.

betterquesting:10.name:8: Where There's a Belt, There's a Way
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
§o"Hoppers are decent at moving items around, but I think I could make something more like rails, only solid so items don't fall through..."
§r
Craft some Conveyor Belts.  They feed items into inventories and hoppers can drop onto them.  Your trusty Hammer can make them change direction or slope.  Redstone can control them as well.

§8§o"Looking Factory--oh! Nice!"

§o§o§r§o"Perhaps if I can combine even more ingredients with this §b§omana§r§o I can create new powers. I'll need a focal point, first..."

§rCreate a §eRunic Altar§r. Using your Lexica Botanica, create Runes of Air, Water, Fire, and Earth.

§o"Wind power is good, but surely I should be able to save it for when I need more."
§r
Create a LV Capacitor which will hold 100K charge. Bang on faces with the Hammer to change mode (blue for in, orange for out).

§o"If I can run this electricity through some heating elements, I bet I can get it hot enough to heat a furnace."§r

Create an External Heater and place it next to a furnace. Then, apply power.

§o"Surely I should be able to combine some of these new Runes I have with the Livingwood to some interesting results."§r

Craft a Rod of the Land and a Rod of the Sea. These rods allow you to create dirt and water blocks using mana, respectively.

There are many different rods with unique abilities. Consider making anything that could help you in your current situation.

§o"I had some ideas while cooking up the Coal - I think I can do something similar with ore."§r

Create enough kiln bricks to build a kiln. The kiln is a type of forge used to create alloys out of two seperate metals.

§o"Using similar materials, I think I might be able to improve even iron."§r

Craft enough bricks to build a crude blast furnace, then make steel.

§o"I have some ideas for some new components, but I'll need a more carefully designed work surface than the top of a block of wood."§r

Craft up an Engineering Workbench.

§o"It might be nice to turn these planks into something climable that I can stack up.  That would make the mills much easier to setup."§r

With treated lumber, you can make climable Scaffold Blocks.

§o"One bucket of this oil seems to be able to treat a batch of lumber.  It feels much stronger after treatment."
§r
Surround the bucket of creosote with planks.

§o"I recall the industrial complexes of the cities back home.  Massive brick ovens could fire coal into coke, and also produced an oil used to treat wood. Perhaps I can replicate this."§r

Craft 27 coke brick blocks.  Assemble the oven by placing them in a 3x3x3 cube and right-clicking with your engineering hammer.  Add coal and a bucket!

§o"Some of the plants around here seem tough enough to weave together into a fabric mesh."
§r
Farm up a good supply of Industrial Hemp.  When ready to harvest, it is tall and not as vibrant.

§o"Over, under... through.  I think I can weave this..."§r

Some upgrades will require a tough fabric to be on hand.
Craft a manasteel sword, pickaxe, shovel, axe, and shears.
Craft a full set of manasteel armor.

§o"I think this fabric might be tough enough to catch even the strongest winds without breaking."§r

Craft enough tough wind panels to upgrade your windmill.  (Right-click with them on a wind mill to upgrade the blades.)

§o"Now that I can create light with power, I think I can make a contraption that will grow plants quickly all day long."§r

Craft a Garden Cloche.
Craft an Alchemy Catalyst, and place it beneath a mana pool to enable §bmana transmutation§r.

§o"If I could harness thermal energy from the earth, I could generate power anywhere, as long as I have a hot and cold block."

§rCraft a Thermoelectric Generator. This machine generates power from the difference in temperature between two adjacent blocks. Place a thermoelectric generator with a block of water on one side and lava on the other.

§o"Treated wood is much sturdier, and fares well against the elements. If I made a storage box out of this, I wouldn't need to drop its contents when I pick it up."

§rCraft a wooden storage crate out of treated wood.

§o"Wind power is fine and good, but the mill needs to be high up for it to work well. With a waterwheel, I could generate power in a smaller space, at any height."

§rCraft 4 Waterwheel Segments, and use them with a steel ingot to craft a Waterwheel. Also, be sure to have a kinetic dynamo on hand.

§o"Water and Lava works fine, but if I had hotter and colder blocks I could increase efficiency."§r

Mine enough uranium to create a Block of Uranium, the hottest block to use with a thermoelectric generator.

Travel to an icy biome and find some Packed Ice, the coldest block to use with a thermoelectric generator.
Craft a Revolver, and 8 Casull Cartridges to use with it.

§o"The Lexicon Botania tells of a flower which can generate mana from bodies of water. Having more ways to gather mana would be very useful."

§rCraft two Hydroangeas in the Petal Apothecary. Place them near a pool of water which they can drink from.

Hydroangeas passively generate mana, but will dissapear after some time.
Craft the Hunter's Handgun from broken parts scattered across the world.

§o"While it's good to have power, all these cables are easy to trip over. Maybe I can craft something to help."§r

Craft some wooden posts and wall mounts to have a better place to anchor wires. Whacking them with your hammer will change the arm configuration.

§o"Sometimes I just need cables to stay right where I want them, regardless of supports. Maybe that fabric can help."§r

Craft a balloon to hold up power fixtures.

§o"With this machinery around, maybe I can knock together a nicer light that doesn't involve fire."§r

Using a single block of glowstone, you can craft 3 lanterns.  These do not require power, but only provide about a glowstone's area of light.

§o"Some parts can be used in a few different ways.  I'll have to jot down those notes."§r

Craft up Common Components Blueprints.

§o"Here at the Engineer's Workbench, I can use my new knowledge of mechanics to create a new solution to my monster problem."

§rAcquire the blueprint "Common Projectiles".
Aquire the blueprint "Metal Press Molds".

§o"Now that I've designed lamps, I think I can upgrade the earlier lantern design.  With enough power, it should spread a lot more light."§r

Powered Laterns shed the same level of light as other forms, but prevent mob spawning for a 32 block radius.  They require LV power, and act as a LV Relay.

§o"By tossing a bar of iron into a mana pool, I can imbue it with mana. I wonder what uses I could put this new material to."§r

Create 4 manasteel ingots by tossing iron ingots into a filled mana pool.

Aquire some magic crystals, then craft a wizard's table, a novice wand, and a spellbook. Magic crystals can be made from crystal flowers or mined underground.

By placing your wand on the wizard's table, you can attune known spellbooks and recharge their mana using magic crystals. When holding a wand, right click to cast a spell. Crouch-scrollwheel will scroll through your list of attuned spells.

Spellbooks, scrolls, and other wizard gear can be found in dungeons, through trading, or as rare drops from monsters.

§o"With all this steel, I think I have a plan to increase power output by... a lot."

§rA squeezer is a large industrial machine used to create§e plant oil§r. Check out the squeezer entry in the Engineer's Manual. Make sure you have all the necessary components, and then check the box once you have finished constructing and powering your squeezer.

§o"With all this steel, I think I have a plan to increase power output by... a lot."

§rA fermenter is a large industrial machine used to generate §eethanol§r from certain fruits, grains, and veggies. Consult the engineer's manual page about the fermenter, ensure you have all the parts required, and check the box once you have built it.

§o"And now, to bring the plan to fruition. A diesel generator is just what I need to kick my power output into overdrive."

§rA diesel generator is a very large industrial machine which generates power from §abiodiesel§r or other combustible fuels. Consult the Engineer's Manual for more information on how to build this machine. Once you have constructed it, check the box to complete the quest.

§o"I think I've devised a way to get Latex from logs, allowing me to build machines requiring plastic."

§rCraft a tree fluid extractor and a latex processing unit. These machines extract latex from logs and craft latex and water into rubber, respectively. Rubber can be burned in a furnace to make plastic, a common crafting component in more advanced machines. Create one unit of plastic.

§o"Given the advancements of steel and my sophisticated power generation system, I think I can do a whole lot better than a pickaxe."

§rCraft a mining drill and a steel drill head.

§o"I've been using iron, gold, etc. to improve my tools and armor. Why not my storage?"

§rCraft an Iron chest.

There are lots of different varieties of chest - from copper to iron to silver to gold to diamond. The diamond chest has the highest storage space.

§nTIP:§r You can move chests and other small entities around by shift-clicking them when nearby. If you would like to shift-click something without picking it up, also hold control.
Craft a Diamond Chest, the highest possible tier of chest

Craft a Sorting upgrade.

This upgrade can be applied to any basic chest (wood, iron, gold, diamond, obsidian, crystal) and adds a sorting menu button at the top of the chest GUI. The chest can then be configured to take or send items from any adjacent sorting chests by assigning certain item priorities.

§nExample:§r Have three adjacent sorting chests, one with metals/ores as high priority, another with tools high priority, and another with food high priority for a simple, rudimentary auto-sorting storage network.

Craft two Ender-Linked Chests.

These chests can be configured with a 3-color code (click with a dye on the top of the chest) and will share an inventory with any other, same-color chest in the world.

Craft a Nether chest.

Just like how one block travelled in the nether is 8 blocks in the overworld, the nether chest seems to compress things stored by a factor of 8. Thus, anything stored in the nether chest has a max stack size of 512 instead of 64.

These strange glowing crystals seem to be filled with a most peculiar energy. Elemental in nature. Would be worth gathering them for the time being but alas I haven't the slightest idea what to do with them. Perhaps I should §a§r§osleep§r on it.

§o"This furniture gives me an idea-something which is practical AND aesthetically pleasing."

§rCraft a storage drawer. Storage drawers can be used to quickly store and take out commonly-used items by right or left clicking. There are varieties that hold one item, two items, or four items at a time.

Storage drawer capacity can be upgraded using drawer upgrades. Search for them in NEI.

Craft a compacting drawer.

Compacting drawers automatically compact items which have multiple states (ie: iron nugget / ingot / block) and allow you to choose which state you want when removing the item. This makes for a very convenient metal storage area.

Craft a Drawer Controller.

This block automatically creates a network out of all adjacent storage drawers, allowing a user to right-click items into the drawer controller rather than the individual drawer. This makes it very easy to put away of items when you have a large amount of drawers in one place.

§o"It would be nice to be able to control my electric lights and machines without having to disconnect all these wires every time..."

§rThere are many cases where you might want to temporarily turn off power to an area. This can be accomplished with a Breaker Switch. Craft one of these now.

Craft a Current Transformer.

In more advanced systems, it may be useful to have an easy-to-access current measurement that you can check often. A voltmeter can be integrated into a power grid using a current transformer, which will tell you the amount of current flowing through when right clicked.

§o"Big plan for big power, step one complete! Step two is GO!"

§rA refinery is a large industrial machine that can refine one or two liquids into another. The most common application is the refining of §ePlant Oil§r and §eEthanol§r into §aBiodiesel§r. Consult the Engineer's Manual for more information on how to build this machine. Ensure you have the required materials, and check the box once you are finished.

§o"In high enough concentrations, mana can be made to teleport short distances rapidly. I will surely need this."
§r
Create Mana sparks.

§o"Interesting.  I dropped a string in the Mana Pool and it altered the fibers.  Perhaps that will be useful."
§r
With a Manaweave outfit, magical operations come easier, costing less mana.

§o"Using sparks and a specialty plate, I'm certain I can focus even more mana into this metal."§r

Craft a terrasteel ingot. Terrasteel is incredibly powerful, but expensive to make. Make sure to check the Lexica Botania for more information on how to obtain it.

§o"There's a strangely named section in the Lexica Botanica about .. elves?  I might be able to send items through a portal to trade for better items."§r

This complex and mana expensive structure opens a trading portal.

§o"I know there has to be a way to infuse these with even MORE mana, but I can't figure it out. The elves might have the secret."
§r
Throw some of your mana infused items through the portal - maybe the Elves might have some ideas.

§o"I'll need to be at the top of my game to defeat this foe. That means the best potions and weapons I have available. Let's see what I can make..."

§rCraft a botanical brewery, and brew a vial of instant health II potion.

Also, craft a set of 4 thorn chakrams, a ranged weapon which pierces enemies and returns to the user.

§o"Looks like I have a fight on my hands. With my botanical knowledge, I think I can make the plants themselves fight for me and guard me."§r

You'll want some flowers to help you in your battle against Gaia. Bellethornes will hurt mobs in an area. Jiyuulia will push mobs away from it, creating a safe space for you. The Fallen Kanade will give you a regeneration effect when nearby.

§o"The pages added to the Lexicon by the elven scribes tell of a ritual to summon a trial of fate. If successful, it says, the will of the gods will be awarded to me."

§rObtain a beacon block and a 4 gaia pylons, which are necessary to summon the Gaia Guardian.
Fight and defeat the Gaia guardian, completing the elven Trial of Fate.

§o"This manasteel is pretty useful.  Besides the normal tools, I bet I can craft some handy things."
§r
There are many useful Baubles and quite a number of decorative ones. Craft some useful ones.
Toss your Lexica Botania into the Alfheim portal to obtain elven knowledge entries.
Empower your Terra Shatterer to the maximum, unlocking its full potential.
Aquire a rainbow oak sapling, and cultivate it to grow unlimited, organic dyes.

§o"Different pieces of gear have different unique qualities - some of them undesirable. With a reforging table, I could re-work a tool, weapon, or armor in hopes of getting something more beneficial."

§rCraft a Reforging Station. This block can be used to re-roll a tool, weapon, armor, or bauble's §oQuality§r modifier.

You can use whatever a tool or armor's repair material is to reforge. Alternatively, you can apply some §ePrismatic Clay§r, which will reforge any item.

Catch every type of water-dwelling creature available by fishing and using the water trap.

§nTIP:§r To see where a given fish can be caught, hold "shift" and hover over it.

§o§o"It seems you can create some liquid starlight by melting the aquamarine in some special basin. The tome I found calls it a lightwell."

§rCraft a Lightwell.

§o"Now to create the materials for my alchemical setup. The Dwarven texts speak of the five metallic aspects that are used in alchemy. These aspects shouldn't be too hard to replicate."

§rCraft the five metal aspectus: iron, copper, lead, silver, and dawnstone. You can place these on the different alchemy pedestals you have situated around your exchange tablet. Next craft the cinder plinth; when provided with ember the plinth will burn any item placed on it into ash, which is used as fuel for the alchemy process. Alchemy recipes will require ash to be placed into specific aspectsus' pedestals between a specific range. This number differs from world to world and recipe to recipe. Consult the ancient codex for more information.

§o"It seems the ancient people of this land left some diagrams that map out the stars. It would be good to find some for my own use." 

§rCheck this once you connect and discover a constellation in the sky.

§o"When I hold the wand, it seems to pull up some star power from the ground. If I dig deep enough I may be able to find some starlight that has crystalized near bedrock."

§rLocate and mine Rock Crystal Ore. (Need diamond or higher to mine)

§r§o"The starlight crystals seem like a good material for tools. I could try to make a pickaxe to help mining some more crystals."

§rCraft a Crystal Pickaxe.

§o§e§o"Good. The crafting table has channeled enough energy for a simple wand, but you will now need something stronger."

§r§o"I'm a little spooked by this voice, but as long as he is helpful I can't complain much."

§rBuild a Luminous Crafting Altar.

§o"The table needs more starlight for what I have planned. Consulting the journal, it seems as if some relays could help me focus even more starlight."

§rFor detailed instructions on how to construct a special relay, consult the Journal. This structure adds more power to astral crafting tables nearby.
Craft a full set of terrasteel armor.

§o"Manasteel tools work quite well, but something made out of this stuff ought to be real special."

§rCraft a terra shatterer. This pickaxe, while quite mundane at first, can be powered up by allowing it to soak in a mana pool and absorb mana. When empowered, the pickaxe will be able to mine large areas at once.

§o"This new material is an improvement upon Manasteel. Perhaps it can improve even my rings."

§rCraft a greater band of aura and a greater ring of magnetization.
Craft a full set of elementium armor.
Craft an elementium sword, pickaxe, shovel, axe, and shears.
Craft a Bauble Case to contain all of your accessories.

§e§o"The crafting altar you made is good, but the time has come for you to harness more power. You are going to need a larger amount of space to contain this altar. Check my Journal for some old schematics of mine."

§rIt seems the mysterious voice is the one who wrote this journal. Consult the astral tome for instructions on how to build the new altar.

§o"Sometimes, relays alone just won't cut it. If I could find an empowered piece of old, I could divine lots of starlight from it. I should build a device to help find one."

§rCraft a Fosic Resonator.§r

§o"Iron ore seems to react to starpower in a way I did not expect - it readily absorbs and holds onto it. If I put enough starpower into some ore, maybe something new will appear."

§rUse the linking tool to direct some starlight from a floating crystal to some iron ore.

Alternatively, find some starmetal ore in the world. Starmetal can be found at extreme heights, above y200.

§nTIP:§r You can craft iron ore using 4 iron clusters.

§o§e§o"The constellations are able to imbue rock crystals with unique energies. By creating an artificial starfield, you can channel a constellation's energy into rock crystals - attuning them to their astral frequency."

§f§o"It looks like I'll need to build something that resembles the night sky. This is going to be a big build - I will need to mine a lot."

§rGather the materials for and construct an attunement altar. Consult the astral tome for more detailed instructions on how to build this structure.

§o§o"It seems I can use some polished rock crystals to redirect the starlight from floating crystals - but it seems to get weaker the further it travels."

§rCraft a Lens.

Craft the following sigils, which consume LP from your network to do useful things.

The §eSigil of the Blood Lamp§r will summon a floating light, using LP from your network.

The §eSigil of Elemental Affinity§r, when activated, provides immunity to drowning, falling, fire, and lava damage. It will, however, drain LP constantly.

The §eSigil of Magnetism§r, when activated, draws in items from a wide radius around you. It will, however, drain LP constantly.

The §eSigil of Holding§r can hold multiple different sigils in one inventory slot. Press "H" by default to access the holding menu. Shift+scroll allows you to swap between held sigils.

§o"Sometimes I only need a sprinkle of starmetal - I should start learning how to grind it down."

§rCraft a grindstone, and grind 4 stardust.

§o"Rock crystals that have been attuned have some interesting properties - I should have them working in a ritual of sorts. Let's build a new structure."

§rConstruct a ritual pedestal - a device (similar to a beacon) which affects the surrounding area differently based on which attuned crystal is placed inside. Detailed instructions are once again in the astral tome.

§o"The astral tome talks of using the stars to travel... not like maps, but acutal teleportation. This warrants some closer investigation."

§rConstruct a gateway structure, and place a gateway in the center. Consult the astral tome for information on how to build this structure. Then, build a second gateway elsewhere to serve as a teleportation destination.

§e§o"It is once again time to improve your altar - this time it is going to be bigger and better than ever before." 

§rCraft a Celestial Altar, then consult the tome for information on how to build a better structure to house the altar.

§o§e§o"You have learned much, and I think it's time I told you of the most powerful crafting altar I developed in my studies. This construct has the power to pull items in from relays, and craft even the most complex astral devices."

§rThe voice now sounds louder and more clear - and once again it speaks, with determination and purpose:

§e§o"This, young stargazer, will be my final message to you. You have come a long way, and yet I have merely given you the basics - there is so much more you can do. Go forth and do as I and countless astral sorcerers before me have done. Explore, test, and uncover the mysteries of the heavens."

- Starmaster Akalis

§rCraft an Iridescent Altar, as well as 4 relays. There is still much to learn about the constellations and the power of the stars - consult the astral tome for more.

§e§o"An important use of starmetal is in making better crystals. Your rock crystals are good, but there is room for improvement." 

§f§o"If I put a rock crystal into a pool of starlight with some starmetal dust, they seem to make a formation. The crystal appears to grow - with focused starlight making this process a bit faster."

§rCreate a Celestial Crystal.

§e§o"Aquamarine, one of the most common components in astral devices, can also be imbued with the power of the stars." 

§f§o"It seems that with the right conditions, more starlight can be put into an Aquamarine gem. I should build an infusion altar like the voice described." 

§rConstruct an Infusion Altar. Once again, consult the astral tome for more detailed instruction. You will need at least twelve buckets of starlight, but it will be worth it in the end.
Aquire a mythical loot chest. You lucky dog!
Have over 5 full bars of health. Now that's dedication!

Mine a substantial amount of Iron Ore, then craft an Iron Hammer.

Hammers are capable of mining a 3x3 square of stone at once, but are slower than pickaxes. They make excellent tools for digging out basements or mining up large veins of ore. 

§T§nTIP:§r An analog of the hammer exists, called the excavator. This can be used to dig out large quantities of dirt/gravel/sand with ease.
Mine nickel, gold, platinum, and uranium ores.

Discover a spectrite gem, a material capable of making the most powerful tools/armors that exist.

Spectrite gems can be found very rarely, typically guarded by powerful monsters. It is said that someone who is a §o"master of the six arts"§r will have an easier time finding it.

§r§r§o"If I could develop a larger filter, prehaps I could purify water in bulk."

§rCraft a Water Filter block. This item must be placed underwater, and can be filled with woven cotton. After a while, the cloth will be consumed and a large amount of fresh water and salt will be generated.

In order to function, the water filter must be placed in the center of a 5x5 area of water source blocks, with the top exposed to air.

The "fresh water" item can be crafted with an empty bottle or canteen to fill it. It can also be used in crafting recipes which require water.

Craft a strainer base. A Water Strainer must be placed one block under flowing water, such that water flows right over top of it. Then, craft a Survivalist's Strainer and place the filter on top of the base. This allows you to passively collect clay, stone, and even ores.

Different types of strainers exist - experiment with them for a change in what is caught.

Craft a Ground Trap. This block can be placed and loaded with bait in order to catch small animals. Over time, the trap will fill with meat. Investigate different types of bait!

Similarly, there is also a Water Trap, which must be placed underwater and will catch fish over time.
Fish up an Immolation Blade from a lake in the nether. You lucky dog!

Aquire an ability totem, either by looting it off a creature or finding it in a chest.

Up to 5 ability totems can be equipped at a time, but each time you die you will drop one at random. Equipping abilities costs experience.

§nTIP:§r Craft an ability bottle to store unwanted abilities.

§o"Now that I've delved into some different arcane arts, I feel confident enough to tackle the complex art of spell inscription."

§rPress the "M" key (default) to open the Magical Psi tutorial. The art of writing your own spells can be quite involved, but the possibilities are nearly endless.

Follow the first tutorial to begin, and this quest should complete its tasks as you go.

§nTIP:§r If you have completed all of the tutorials and want inspiration for new spells, consider checking out §e/r/psispellcompendium§r on reddit

§l§6§lPack Modes:
§r- There are two ways to play this pack: §o§e§oNormal Mode§r, and §o§e§oNo-Class Mode§r. 
- §e§oNormal Mode§r: most recipes will be locked to you at the start, and will be gradually unlocked based on your chosen classes (professions and magic disciplines). 
- §o§e§oNo-Class Mode§r: everything is unlocked from the beginning, for a more classic experience.

§o§lTo select §e§o§lNo-Class Mode§r§o, §lenter the following command: 
§e/give @s contenttweaker:class_book
§r
§lQuesting:§r
- This quest book is meant to serve as a guide through the various mods of the pack. 
- This is a work in progress, and will be the focus of many longer-term updates.
- The questbook must be updated whenever a change is made. The quest gui should prompt you to update all on its own, but if this does not occur you may use the debug wand to manually update the questbook.

§lPerformance:§r
- For everybody: If you are on a lower-end PC I recommend installing §ooptifine§r, fantastic mod which WILL give you a performance increase. Make sure to install the latest version. If you install optifine and report a bug or crash, please tell us that optifine is present!
- If you are still having performance issues, §odynamic surroundings§r features can be disabled via the mod options menu and § §r§obetter foliage§r can be disabled in the "F8" menu.
- If dynamic lights are giving you issues, they can be disabled by pressing "L". If you suffer severe lag in the nether, try this.

§lBackups:§r
- §oFTB Backups allows for scheduled, incremental backups. By default, a backup will occur every 30 minutes. This can be changed in the file: "config/ftbutilities.cfg"
- Backups can be manually performed with the command "/backup start"
- Backups are saved as .zip files in a folder called "backups" in the minecraft directory.

§o"Exploring the underground, I've found samples of regional flora which grow nuggets of metal! I should collect more of these useful plants."

§rMine up some different variants of oreberry bushes.

Oreberries are rare plants which slowly grow metal nuggets in darkness. Oreberries can be found all across the world, but certain variants only grow in certain biomes.

§o"Now that I've established a steady source of food, I should see about turning a profit from it!"

§rCraft an Order Board. This board will fill up with cooking bounties - requests for food from hungry creatures in the world. Completing these bounties will net you lots of coins, but beware! Once a bounty is accepted, you have limited time to complete it before it disappears.

§o"Framed blocks have really opened up new building options for me, but I want to build with some... less-traditional shapes."

§rCraft an Architect's Sawbench. This table can be used to turn blocks into fancy shapes, such as angled roof tiles, stairway bannisters, pillars, or archways. Experiment with it and use these fancy blocks to open up new potential for your builds!

Collect some of the different stones found underground.

Fancy stones can be useful for building/decorating, and are occasionally used in recipes. Similarly to ores, the various stones can be found in different biomes.

§r§lPurple Slate -§r §oHot Biomes
§r§lGreen Slate -§r §oTemp Biomes
§r§lChalk -§r §oSandy, Water

§o"If I had a proper kitchen like back home, I could prepare food with ease. I should see about assembling a food prep area in my home."

§rCraft the following pieces of a kitchen, then assemble a kitchen multiblock structure by placing the blocks adjacent to one another.

The cooking table allows easy crafting of the full list of all craftable food items using them ingredients in connected counters and cabinets. Kitchenware from mods like harvestcraft can also be placed on tool racks to provide them to recipes.
Craft two modern couches, four modern lights, a ceiling fan, and a light switch.
Craft a basin, a bath, a toilet, and two wall cabinets.

Craft a washing machine and a dish washer.

These two machines can be filled with soap and used to repair armor and tools, respectively.

§o"I have been researching the ancient Dwarves for some time now, and something is irking me. Why all these machinations of war alongside such marvels? Texts indicate the Dwarves and Astrals were locked in a sort of land and sky conflict which caused the collapse of advanced civilization on this continent. Furthermore, I believe the Dwarves won this war. Their texts mention 'usurping the cosmos' whatever that means, but I believe it has something to do with a curious crystal found at high peaks. Aetherium."
§r
Aetherium is a powerful material found at extremely high elevations and in very small veins. You will need at least a diamond pickaxe or equivilent to mine it. It is also said that aetherium is bestowed as a blessing from the gods, if the caller's offering is found worthy.

Collect a small stockpile of 12 aetherium shards to begin your foray into Aetherworks.

§o"Aetherium seems to be formed in a similar manner to Crystaline Ember; only instead of the core of the world's energy solidifying within bedrock, aetherium is the energy of the cosmos condensing at great altitudes. This process is extremely slow, however, and naturally ocurring aetherium is rare. Maybe I can speed up this process with a construct of my own."§r

Create the moonlight amplifier multiblock. Simply put, this structure will generate impure aetherium liquid at night.

First craft a fluid vessel, two aetherium prism supports, and an aetherium prism. Next gather 12 archaic brick blocks, and 8 archaic edges. Finally, craft four moonlight amplifiers and four aetherium lens focusing matrixes.

Once all the materials are acquired, you can begin the construction of the multiblock. First place the fluid vessel in a large open space; stack on top of it two aetherium prism supports and finally the aetherium prism. Next create a ring of archaic brick blocks around the fluid vessel two blocks away from the vessel's faces and one block away diagonally. The ring should be two blocks tall on the face sides and one block tall on the diagonal sides. Next place an archaic edge on top of each archaic brick. Finally place the four moonlight amplifiers on the three block tall pillars with the flat side facing the prism in the center, and the aetherium focusing matrixes on the two block tall pillars diagonal to the fluid vessel. 

Done properly, your structure should look like this:

If everything is correctly lined up, the textures of the archaic brick should change, signifying the multiblock is active:

§o"It seems that one should not rush natural phenomena. The aetherium generated through my homemade structure is too raw for normal use. I'll need to refine this cosmic slurry with something slightly mystical, and able to channel the energy that courses through aetherium. Perhaps electrum?"§r

Create a bucket of aetherium. Aetherium can be made rather simply by piping impure aetherium and molten electrum into a mixer centrifuge. The two will alloy together and create aetherium, which can be picked up in a metal or clay bucket from a fluid vessel.

§o"The Book of Natural Aura talks about a force known as Aura, which can be utilized in various rituals. I should study how to harness this power."

§rRead the beginnings of the Book of Natural Aura.  

Craft some brilliant fibers, and touch them to the leaves of a tree and wait for golden leaves to spread throughout the tree. Break the golden leaves in order to obtain Gold Leaf, which is used in various rituals.
§oCraft a full set of Sylvan armor.

Gather the different types of quartz which can be found in the overworld: basic (nether) quartz, certus quartz, and charged certus quartz. Charged certus quartz is found deeper undergroud than its uncharged counterpart.

Certus and nether quartz are the most basic crafting pieces necessary to make a ME (matter-energy) system. ME systems can handle crafting and storage on a large scale.

To read more, check out the AE2 website online here:
§ehttps://ae-mod.info/

Create 8 fluix crystals.

Fluix crystals are important for crafting the components of an ME system. Fluix crystals are grown by dropping one nether quartz, one charged certus quartz, and one redstone together into a pool of water. After a few seconds, two fluix crystals are created.

Craft a quartz grindstone, as well as a wooden crank.

The grindstone is a simple device powered by the wooden crank, which can grind quartz or fluix crystals into dust. The crank must be placed atop the grindstone and manually clicked in order to grind the crystals placed inside.

Use the grindstone to grind 4 quartz and 4 fluix. Then, smelt the quartz powder into silicone using a furnace.

We finally have all the components necessary to create a rudimentary ME system. The simplest ME system consists of a storage component, an interface, and a power intake. To accomplish this, we will need the following:

- 1x ME Chest
- 1x 1k Storage Cell
- 1x Energy Acceptor
- 1x ME Terminal
- 4x Fluix Glass Cable

Place these machines, either adjacent or connected via fluix glass cables. The ME chest accepts one storage cell, which can be accessed either from the top of the chest or from a connected ME terminal. Items can be inserted or removed in this way, until the storage cell has reached capacity. In order to keep this system running, power must be supplied through a connected energy acceptor. Once assembled, you should have a simple, ME-based storage system!

§nTIP:§r The rewards for this quest include the ME Storage Bus. This item allows an adjacent inventory (like a standard chest) to be accessed from the ME network.

Craft a block extender, a sorting interface, and some sorting connector pipes.

The block extender extends the faces of any block it is facing in a configurable way. For example, if you wanted to access the top of a furnace with two hoppers, you can use a block extender to "extend" the top face of the furnace and input the hopper to the extender.

The sorting interface allows you to add sorting network capability to any block, similarly to sorting chests. This allows you to add storage drawers, furnaces, bookshelves, or other inventories to a sorting network.

Sorting connector pipes allow you to connect sorting blocks (chests, interfaces) together without them being adjacent to one another.

Craft a charger.

The charger, when supplied with power, will charge any item placed inside it. Using a charger is a more reliable way of obtaining charged certus quartz when compared to mining.

Pure crystals can be grown and multiplied using seeds, which are crafted using 1x crystal dust and 1x sand. Nether quartz, certus quartz, and fluix crystal seeds can be crafted in this way. Seeds are grown slowly when immersed in water, and will not despawn. Growing a crystal fully yields a pure crystal of that variety, which is required for some certain crafting recipes.

Craft 4 fluix crystal seeds, and grow them into 4 pure fluix crystals. 

§nTIP:§r Crystal growth speed can be raised by crafting and powering a Crystal Growth Accelerator

Craft an inscriber, then use the inscriber to craft 4 logic processors.

In the last quest, you should have recieved two press molds as a reward. These molds are used in a machine called the inscriber, which must be powered with electricity to function. The silicone mold allows you to make printed silicone using raw silicone. The logic mold allows you to make a printed logic circuit using a gold ingot. When the printed silicone and printed logic circuit are combined with redstone, the result is a finished logic processor. This is the final component of the basic machines involved in an ME system.

In order to expand the network, we will need more sophisticated equipment. Craft the following useful pieces of equipment:

- 1x ME Controller
- 1x ME Crafting Terminal
- 1x ME Drive
- 1x Energy Cell

An ME Controller functions as a routing hub for an ME network, and is used to manage networks with more than 8 connected devices. An ME Crafting Terminal allows for items to be crafted directly from the ME network interface. An ME Drive allows for up to 8 storage cells to be placed in one block, and also shows fullness of the cells via lights on the block itself. An Energy Cell allows for energy to be stored in the ME network, similarly to a capacitor.

§nTIP:§r Tired of looking at unsightly ME cables? A Cable Facade can be crafted with any block surrounded by 4 cable anchors. These can be used to hide cables behinds a decorative wall, or create a solid surface for levers or buttons.

Obtain and use the Build Reach Upgrade 1, which unlocks a new building mode via the mod "Effortless Building". These modes allow for blocks to be placed in special ways that make building large structures effortless.

Build modes are toggled by pressing the build radial menu key, which is §eLeft-ALT§r by default.
- Normal: vanilla placement
- Normal+: increased reach
- Line: place lines of blocks in any 3 axis
- Wall: place walls in x or z axis
- Floor: place 'walls' in y axis

Mirror and Array modes are toggled by pressing the mirror key, which is §eNumpad Plus§r by default. These modes allow for blocks to be placed in a mirrored or symmetrical way.

§nTIP:§r The reward for this quest is a randomizer bag! This item can be filled with various blocks, and when used, will place a random block from its inventory.
Craft and consume the Range Upgrade 3, which allows you to place blocks up to 200 blocks away. Wow!

Craft a Storage Cabinet

The storage cabinet allows for only a single type of item to be placed, but allows for different variants of that item to be contained as well. For example, a single storage cabinet could hold over a hundred enchanted books or potions, which would take up space in a regular chest.

§o"Aetherium is a very raw and powerful material, and will require quite a bit of force in it's working. Perhaps if I replicate one of the great dawnstone forges of antiquity I'll have some better luck."§r

Gather materials for your Aetherium Forge. These consist of nine dawnstone blocks placed in a 3x3 square, and an aetherium forge core placed in the center. Simply right click a dawnstone block with your tinker's hammer and the multiblock will be formed.

§o"The Aetherium Forge will require some delicate equipment to function properly, as well as a massive ammount of ember to fuel it. I should begin gathering materials. Working with Aetherium is going to be an arduous process."§r

Craft the pieces nessicary to begin using the aetherium forge: A forge heater, forge vent, and an aetherium ingot former. Power the heater with ember (as well as the forge controller), and place a source of heat under the heater. The vents can be used to keep heat from building too rapidly Then place a fluid vessel full of aetherium beside the forge. Place a dawnstone ingot or plate in the ingot former, and an aetherium version will be created. Use these aetherium plates and ingots to create an Aetherium Anvil.

Craft a Statue Chisel, and build a statue of yourself!

The statue chisel allows you to chisel statues of players out of blocks. Place two of the same block vertically, then click on the top block with the statue chisel to make a statue! You can change properties such as pose and player name.

Once a statue is chiselled, you can equip items on its armor slots or its hands by interacting with it.

You can also paint a statue by clicking on it using a palette!

Craft the neccesary items to construct an area suitable for performing the Ritual of the Forest. For layout help, consult the Book of Natural Aura.

Once the ritual circle has been constructed, perform the ritual to craft some Tokens of Joy. There are four types of tokens which are commonly used in aura-related crafting recipes.

Build 4 oak bridge blocks.

Bridge blocks serve as an easy way to make aesthetically appealing bridges, docks, and platforms. A high variety of bridge types are available, and they can be made into "bridge end" blocks via the crafting window.

§o"With my newfound knowledge of agriculture, I can now forage for seeds in wild gardens across the land."

§rBust up some garden blocks to forage wild fruits and veggies! Gather corn, onion, tomato, and strawberry - then convert them into seeds in the crafting window.

Craft a Fertile Apiary and an Industrious Apiary.

The Fertile Apiary accepts Queen Bees, and produces wax, comb, and grubs. When the Queen reaches the end of her life, royal jelly will be produced, which can be crafted to obtain a new queen.

The Industrious Apiary accepts Worker Bees, and produces honeycomb only. It will also provide a small growth boost to any nearby crops.

Craft an animal rancher.

This machine accepts power to shear sheep and milk cows within its vicinity.

Craft some basic foodstuffs.

§n§oTIP:§r §oHaving a functional kitchen makes cooking a lot easier! Go do the quest "Kitchen Beginnings" in the Farming Basics tab first.
Prepare the following meals.
Create some advanced dishes.
Prepare some truly complex dishes.

Craft a presser, which allows you to press certain raw food ingredients to yield other ingredients.

An important use of the press is to obtain honey and wax from honeycomb. Obtain 4 honey and 4 wax.
Sometimes, the right plant can be hard to find. Craft a market block, which lets you trade coins for specific crop seeds.

Craft a grinder, which lets you craft certain food materials at a better rate than at the workbench.

Use your new grinder to craft 16 flour (inputting any grain will yield flour).

Craft a plant fertilizer.

This machine accepts power and bonemeal, and will fertilize any crops in its vicinity.

Craft a resources fisher.

This machine accepts power and will automatically fish when placed over a pool of water.

Craft a plant interactor!

This machine accepts power and allows you to harvest any interact-able crops. How useful!

§n§oTip:§r§o If machines are not harvesting inside of claimed chunks, try raising the permissions of "fake players" in your team settings.

Use a bucket to bring water to the spot where you would like your farm to be, then till the soil around it using the hoe. Plant your seeds and wait until they are fully grown.

TIP: You can quickly harvest crops with right-click.

§r§r§o"Drinking dirty water is no fun. If I could develop a filter, I could purify water on the go!"

§rThere are two ways to purify bottles of dirty water. First, bottles may be purified by boiling them in a furnace. Secondly, bottles and buckets of water may be filtered by crafting them with a charcoal filter.

Craft some charcoal filters, and obtain some bottles of purified water.
Similarly to the ground trap, a water trap can be used to passively catch fish. Craft a water trap, and 8 water bait.

Using a bottle and cork, aura can be bottled and stored for use in crafting as well as rituals.

Craft some Bottle and Cork, then right-click with it in the overworld to get Bottled Sunlight.

A Bottle and Cork may be used in other dimensions as well, to store different types of air.

This machine accepts power in order to smelt items, furnace-style.
