Craft a simple SAG mill.

This machine accepts power in order to grind materials down to dust.

§o§nTIP:§r§o All simple machines will slowly leak power - with more advanced Engineering knowledge, they could be upgraded.

Craft a simple stirling generator.

This machine accepts furnace fuel, and converts it to electricity.

§o§nTIP:§r§o All simple machines will slowly leak power - with more advanced Engineering knowledge, they could be upgraded.

Craft a simple alloy furnace.

This machine accepts power in order to smelt items. Unlike a normal furnace, the alloy furnace has multiple inputs and can combine certain materials.

§o§nTIP:§r§o All simple machines will slowly leak power - with more advanced Engineering knowledge, they could be upgraded.

Craft a simple wired charger.

This machine accepts power in order to charge any handheld electrical items placed inside.

§o§nTIP:§r§o All simple machines will slowly leak power - with more advanced Engineering knowledge, they could be upgraded.

Craft a simple crafter.

This machine accepts power in order to craft items together. This can be very handy for automating complex tasks.

§o§nTIP:§r§o All simple machines will slowly leak power - with more advanced Engineering knowledge, they could be upgraded.

Gather some §9grains of infinity§r, a fragment of the world beyond - distilled.

Grains of infinity can sometimes be obtained by setting fire to bedrock and allowing it to snuff out naturally. It can also be dropped from mobs with connections to the End, and found as loot in certain chests.

Iron gears can be obtained by trading with villagers, or stamped by someone with knowledge of Engineering.

§c§lNote: §r§cIn order to progress though this quest tree, the "Automation" quest page should first be completed.

A basic material used when performing sanguimancy is demonic will, which can be extracted from hostile creatures.

Craft a rudimentary snare. Then, throw the snare at a hostile mob and slay it. If done correctly, the mob should drop its §bdemonic will§r.

Craft a Hellfire Forge, then use the forge to create a Petty Tartaric Gem.

The hellfire forge allows for the crafting of tartaric gems, which store large amounts of will, and sigils, which consume will to perform certain actions.

To create a Petty Tartaric Gem, place one glass block, lapis lazuli, gold ingot, and redstone dust in the four squares in the outer ring of the hellfire forge. Then, place §bdemonic will §rin the far right slot in order to power the forge.

Craft a sentient sword, by combining one petty tartaric gem and an iron sword in the hellfire forge.

The sentient sword is able to bind souls without requiring the use of snares. Additionally, the sword's power scales with the amount of §bdemonic will§r held in the largest soul gem in the inventory.

Craft a blood altar, and a sacrificial dagger.

The altar may be filled with §clife essence §r(also known as §clife points§r, or §cLP§r)§r by right-clicking next to it with a sacrificial dagger. Life essence is a resource which is used to perform powerful rituals. Five hearts of sacrifice is the equivalent of one bucket worth of essence.

Create a weak blood orb, by infusing a diamond with life essence at a blood altar.

A blood orb can be used to sacrifice anywhere, depositing life essence directly into your §cblood network§r. Most rituals will pull essence from your blood network to power themselves.

§o§nTIP:§r§o Trying to pull LP from an empty network will fail and give you nausea. Be careful not to run on empty!

Higher tier blood altars can store more essence, allowing you to perform higher-level infusions. Upgrade your blood altar to tier II by creating a structure around it. For a tier II altar, you will need to place 8 blank rune blocks below the altar in a circle around it. 

Obtain 16 blank slates, then use them to craft 8 blank rune blocks and upgrade your altar.

§oFor reference, see the images here:
§ehttps://ftb.gamepedia.com/Blood_Altar

Craft a rune of self-sacrifice.

This rune may be used in place of a blank rune in blood altar construction. Each rune of self-sacrifice increases the amount of LP added to the altar when using a sacrificial dagger.

Infusing a redstone block at the blood altar, creating an apprentice blood orb.

Higher tier blood orbs can store more LP in their blood network.

Craft a rune of capacity.

This rune may be used in place of a blank rune in blood altar construction. Each rune of capacity increases the amount of LP which can be stored in the altar.

Craft a sentient armor gem, by combining an obsidian block, iron block, and diamond chestplate in a hellfire forge.

The gem can be used to equip sentient armor, provided a minimum of 16 demonic will is held in the inventory. The more §bdemonic will§r is contained in the largest soul gem in your inventory, the more protective the armor will be.

Craft a full set of sentient tools, and a sentient bow.

Sentient equipment scales in effectiveness with the amount of §bwill§r held in the largest soul gem in your inventory.

§§§o§nTIP:§r §oIf a special type of tartaric gem is held, sentient items gain additional effects on use.

Obtain a §6divination sigil§r, allowing you to view the essence in your blood network at a glance.

First, craft §earcane ashes§r by combining redstone, bonemeal, gunpowder, and coal in a hellfire forge. Place arcane ash on the ground to form a runic circle, then right-click wiht a piece of redstone to make a divination rune.

Finally, you must bind the rune to a tablet. Craft a §eblank slate§r by infusing a stone block in the blood altar. Once you have your slate, simply right-click the divination rune with it to complete the ritual.

Obtain a Water Sigil, Lava Sigil, and a Sigil of the Blood Lamp.

These sigils are crafted just like the divination sigil, except you will need to add a water reagent, lava reagent, or blood lamp reagent to your arcane ash circle instead of redstone dust. Then, simply add a blank slate to finish the sigil.

The §eWater Sigil§r and §eLava Sigil§r will create source blocks of their respective liquid, using LP from your blood network.

Upgrade your blood altar to tier IV, then imbue a weak blood shard at the altar to create a master blood orb.

To construct a tier IV blood altar, you will need to place blank runes one block below and two blocks out from the previous level - leaving a one block gap between which can be filled with any block. 7 blank runes will be placed on each side, leaving a 2x2 space at the corners empty. At the edge of each corner, build upwards 4 blocks and then place a large bloodstone brick block atop the pillar.

§ehttps://ftb.gamepedia.com/Blood_Altar

Upgrade your blood altar to tier IV, then imbue a nether star at the altar to create an archmage blood orb.

To construct a tier IV blood altar, you will need to place blank runes one block below and three blocks out from the previous level - leaving a two block gap between which can be filled with any block. 13 blank runes will be placed on each side, leaving a 2x2 space at the corners empty. Finally, place a beacon block atop each corner. 

§oFor reference, see the images here:
§ehttps://ftb.gamepedia.com/Blood_Altar

Craft the following sigils, which consume LP from your network to do useful things.

The §eSeer's Sigil§r, an upgrade to the divination sigil, allows you to see the amount of blood stored in an altar, progress of any blood infusions at that altar, and altar power when held.

The §eSigil of Air§r allows you to burst through the air with speed. It makes for a good escape and travel tool.

The §eSigil of Elasticity§r, when activated, will save you from a high fall by turning your body elastic. It is well used alongside the Sigil of Air.

The §eSigil of the Fast Miner§r, when activated, will give you a Haste II buff.

The §eSigil of the Green Grove§r, when activated, will advance the growth of nearby crops. It can also be used as an infinite bonemeal source, consuming LP.

Obtain a Bound Blade, a powerful, unbreakable sword which draws blood from your network and allows you to collect blood shards when slaying mobs.

First, obtain a binding reagent, and add it to an arcane ash sigil. Place a diamond sword within, and step back!

The sword can be un-sheathed with right-click, and will slowly drain LP when in use.

§o§nTIP:§r§o Experiment with other Bound Tools! They are extremely powerful, and can consume LP to break many blocks at once.

Craft a full set of Living Armor.

Living armor "learns" as you wear it, adding powerful upgrades to itself over time.

Craft an Incense Altar, a device which can be placed nearby the blood altar to grant a bonus to LP when self-sacrificing.

The altar can be upgraded by creating certain structures underneath it, or adding certain blocks around that increase "Tranquility".
